Ports:
------
Port numbers are used as Point of communication

linux system has 65,000 port numbers available

0-1000 ==> reserved by linux


ssh - port 22
http - port 80
https - port 443
telnet - port 23


netstat (network statsics)
-------------------------
command is used to list all listnening & active ports

syntax: netstat -lntp




--------------------------------
Linux OS:
---------
linux operating system has 2 major distributions.

1. RHEL Family (Red Hat Enterprise Linux)
   
   Common Distributions: Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL), CentOS , Fedora
   Best suited for business and enterprise environments
   Support: Commercial support available (paid plans, official technical support)

   Package Manager: yum or dnf (used for managing software packages)
   Package Format: .rpm (Red Hat Package Manager format)  

   yum install  git ==> it will download the git.rpm file ==> install the git from the downloaded rpm file 

   

2. Debian Family
   Common Distributions: Debian & Ubuntu (most popular Debian-based distribution)
   Widely used by developers, open-source communities, and personal users
   Support: Free and community-based support (forums, Stack Overflow, etc.)

   Package Manager: apt (Advanced Package Tool)
   Package Format: .deb (Debian package format)




-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to check OS related info in linux ?

cat /etc/os-release

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

top
-------
 Top Command is used to check which process utilizing what % of CPU & What % of Memory(RAM)
 Top command helps in understanding system performance.

 top -u <username>  ==> Shows processes for a specific user.

