variables:
----------
Variables are memory location which can store some values.

syntax: <variable_name>=<variable_value>
        variable="value" → storing data
        $variable → using the stored data
  

How to print / check / substitute / call values of a variable?
--------------------------------------------------------------

$ (dollar) is mandatory while substituting varaible ==> $<variable_name>

echo $<variable_name>


Example 1:
 PLAYER=viratKohli
 echo " my favorite sportsmen is $PLAYER "


Example 2: 
  user_name="devopsAdmin"
  echo "Hello, $user_name! How are you today?"

Example 3: 
 
[ec2-user@my-server-1 ~]$ project="DevOps"
[ec2-user@my-server-1 ~]$ echo "$project project started"
DevOps project started

#Now changing value of same variable:

[ec2-user@my-server-1 ~]$ project="CloudMigration"
[ec2-user@my-server-1 ~]$ echo "$project project started"
CloudMigration project started


Example 4: Multiple Variables
[ec2-user@my-server-1 ~]$ user="admin"
[ec2-user@my-server-1 ~]$ server="10.0.0.25"
[ec2-user@my-server-1 ~]$ echo "Login with $user to $server"
Login with admin to 10.0.0.25
